<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF3FFC2FEF7FEA33C53FEDC" box="[275,343,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,533,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-159@2.[151,1436,525,1910]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Habitus 1 N. ingentis; 2 N. resimus; 3 N. leigongensis; 4 N. yujiei; 5 N. muricatus; 6 N. excertus; 7 N. serratus. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6554672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6554672/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) dark brown; legs yellowish brown; antennae dark brown to light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF3FFC2FF23FECF3828FE14" blockId="2.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
Head (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF3FFC2FEF4FECF3C5BFEF8" box="[272,351,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1396,1420]" captionTargetBox="[153,1422,191,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-30@4.[151,1437,181,1372]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Nazeris resimus 13 forebody; 14 male sternite VII; 15 male sternite VIII; 16 aedeagus in ventral view; 17 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13 1.0 mm; 14–17 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552151/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) 1.08–1.16 times as long as wide; punctation very dense, moderately coarse, distinctly umbilicate, interstices lacking microsculpture; postocular portion approximately 1.6–2.0 times as long as eye length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF3FFC2FF23FE173E6CFE68" blockId="2.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF3FFC2FEA1FE173C92FE30" box="[325,406,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1396,1420]" captionTargetBox="[153,1422,191,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-30@4.[151,1437,181,1372]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Nazeris resimus 13 forebody; 14 male sternite VII; 15 male sternite VIII; 16 aedeagus in ventral view; 17 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13 1.0 mm; 14–17 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552151/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) 1.14–1.16 times as long as wide, 0.89–0.92 times as long and 0.85–0.91 times as broad as head; punctation non-umbilicate, moderately dense and as coarse as that of head; midline posteriorly with short and narrow impunctate elevation; interstices lacking microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<caption id="579B57D2FFF3FFC2FF73F8093C65F854" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6554672" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6554672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6554672/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" startId="2.[151,264,1933,1957]" targetBox="[161,1436,533,1906]" targetPageId="2">
