</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF2FFC3FF23F9993885F9C6" blockId="3.[151,1437,1565,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF2FFC3FEFAF9993C75F9AA" box="[286,369,1565,1591]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1396,1420]" captionTargetBox="[153,1422,191,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-30@4.[151,1437,181,1372]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Nazeris resimus 13 forebody; 14 male sternite VII; 15 male sternite VIII; 16 aedeagus in ventral view; 17 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13 1.0 mm; 14–17 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552151/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) 0.65–0.71 times as long as wide, 0.57–0.63 times as long and 0.97–1.00 times as broad as pronotum; punctation as dense as, and slightly coarser than that of pronotum; interstices lacking microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF2FFC3FF23F9E13932F93E" blockId="3.[151,1437,1565,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Abdomen with punctation dense and rather coarse on tergites III–V, dense and less coarse on tergite VI, moderately dense and fine on tergites VII–VIII; interstices lacking microsculpture.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF2FFC3FF23F9293833F8A9" blockId="3.[151,1437,1565,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Male. Sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF2FFC3FE47F9293CF1F95A" box="[419,501,1709,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1396,1420]" captionTargetBox="[153,1422,191,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-30@4.[151,1437,181,1372]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Nazeris resimus 13 forebody; 14 male sternite VII; 15 male sternite VIII; 16 aedeagus in ventral view; 17 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13 1.0 mm; 14–17 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552151/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin shallowly emarginated in the middle. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF2FFC3FAA6F9293890F955" box="[1346,1428,1709,1736]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1396,1420]" captionTargetBox="[153,1422,191,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-30@4.[151,1437,181,1372]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Nazeris resimus 13 forebody; 14 male sternite VII; 15 male sternite VIII; 16 aedeagus in ventral view; 17 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13 1.0 mm; 14–17 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552151/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) with V-shaped posterior excision. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF2FFC3FD76F9553E16F976" box="[658,786,1745,1771]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1396,1420]" captionTargetBox="[153,1422,191,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-30@4.[151,1437,181,1372]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Nazeris resimus 13 forebody; 14 male sternite VII; 15 male sternite VIII; 16 aedeagus in ventral view; 17 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13 1.0 mm; 14–17 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552151/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Figs 16, 17</figureCitation>
) moderately sclerotized; with ventral process long, dorsal parts slightly widened near middle in ventral view, with ventrad process near apex in lateral view; dorso-lateral apophyses with curved and very thin apical portions in ventral view, not reaching apex of ventral process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4BFE54D1FFF2FFC3FF23F8B93C04F87A" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF2FFC3FF23F8B93E6BF8E1" blockId="3.[151,1437,1565,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF2FFC3FF23F8B93F36F8CA" bold="true" box="[199,562,1853,1879]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Distribution and habitat data.</emphasis>
The species is known from Leigong Mt. in eastern 
<collectingRegion id="C120C9B8FFF2FFC3FB60F8B939ECF8CA" box="[1156,1256,1853,1879]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
. The specimens were collected by sifting leaf litter at altitudes of 
<quantity id="C41CAABFFFF2FFC3FD5BF8E53E6FF8E1" box="[703,875,1889,1916]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.15" metricValueMin="1.55" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" unit="m" value="1850.0" valueMax="2150.0" valueMin="1550.0">
<geoCoordinate id="66D0619DFFF2FFC3FD5BF8E53FF9F8E1" box="[703,765,1889,1916]" degrees="1,550" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" precision="55" value="1.55">1,550</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="66D0619DFFF2FFC3FD18F8E53E4FF8E1" box="[764,843,1889,1916]" degrees="2,150" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" precision="55" value="-2.15">–2,150</geoCoordinate>
m
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF2FFC3FF23F8013C04F87A" blockId="3.[151,1437,1565,2023]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF2FFC3FF23F8013CB7F802" bold="true" box="[199,435,1925,1951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The new species is distinguished from all the known species of 
<taxonomicName id="C4E47CD9FFF2FFC3FB79F80239F7F802" box="[1181,1267,1926,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF2FFC3FB79F80239F7F802" box="[1181,1267,1926,1951]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Nazeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion id="C120C9B8FFF2FFC3FAD8F8013898F802" box="[1340,1436,1925,1951]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
and adjacent area by the distinctive shape of the aedeagus, particularly the very thin apical portions in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF2FFC3FF44F8493DF7F87A" box="[160,243,1997,2023]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1396,1420]" captionTargetBox="[153,1422,191,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-30@4.[151,1437,181,1372]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13–17. Nazeris resimus 13 forebody; 14 male sternite VII; 15 male sternite VIII; 16 aedeagus in ventral view; 17 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13 1.0 mm; 14–17 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552151/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
