<subSubSection id="4BFE54D1FFF5FFC4FF23FA5A3CCDF981" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF5FFC4FF23FA5A3CCDF981" blockId="4.[151,1437,1502,1564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF5FFC4FF23FA5A3C4AFA65" bold="true" box="[199,334,1502,1528]" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: curved) alludes to the curved apical portions of dorso-lateral apophyses of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
